Q13. What will be the output of the following TypeScript code?
function greet(name: string, age: number = 25): string {
  return `Hello, my name is ${name} and I am ${age} years old.`;
}
console.log(greet("John"));
1. A) Hello, my name is John and I am years old.
2. B) Hello, my name is John and I am 25 years old.
3. C) Hello, my name is John and I am undefined years old.
4. D) Hello, my name is John and I am NaN years old.
